benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/invoicePayments/{paymentId}/tags - Add tags to payment

covered: Valid Payload scenarios (TC01-TC04): successful creation with valid payload and metadata
Invalid Payloads (TC08, TC09, TC10, TC16, TC17) – malformed JSON, invalid UUIDs, extra fields, null elements
Duplicate submission handling (TC11) – dedup to a single tag
Large payloads / boundary testing (TC12, TC14) – performance and boundary size
Server error handling (TC13) – 503 when dependency unavailable
Validation of IDs (TC06, TC09) – invalid paymentId and invalid tag definition UUID formats
Idempotency with existing tag (TC19) – no duplicates when tag already exists
Partial input / nulls (TC17) – invalid input handling
Empty array (TC04) – empty payload yields empty result
gaps: Rate limiting / throttling scenarios not tested
Caching behavior / ETag and Cache-Control headers not tested
Empty request body (no payload) scenario not explicitly tested
500 Internal Server Error scenarios not covered (beyond 503)
Content-Type / Accept header edge cases not explored
recommendations: Add tests for rate limiting to verify throttling and stability under load (per POST), especially under concurrent requests
Introduce caching tests to validate ETag and Cache-Control headers for POST responses
Add a test for an explicitly empty request body (no payload) to confirm proper handling
Add 500 Internal Server Error simulations (e.g., database failure) to ensure proper 5xx handling
Consider edge-case tests around content-type negotiation and Accept header variations
